<plot>The well-ordered life of Dylan Thomas (Robert Tobin), a high-priced male escort, goes into moral free-fall beginning with the night he impulsively takes home a young woman he finds passed out drunk on a sidewalk. A sad little stray cat in a lycra dress and Prada shoes, Allison Campbell (Melissa Muniz) is looking for security or love, and she may not know the difference. While Dylan plies his trade in swank hotels, a tentative domestic relationship with seemingly homeless Allison evolves, based on the illusion that neither of them has a past. Voyeurism is the dramatic strategy and the engaging lure for this revealing story, the 25th film to be certified as a Dogma 95 production.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?114886</url></doc>
